# App Architecture

## Tech Stack

- Frontend: React 18, Vite 6, Tailwind CSS, React Router DOM, Framer Motion
- Backend: Node.js (ES modules), Express 4, Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth)
- Template Writer: Python (openpyxl) called via child_process from Node.js
- AI: Claude Haiku for account classification
- Integrations: QuickBooks Online (intuit-oauth), Excel/CSV (xlsx library)

## Key Directories

```
client/src/screens/     — Page components (InputEngine, Dashboard, Onboarding)
client/src/components/  — Reusable UI (InputField, OwnerPaySlider, MappingConfirmation)
client/src/context/     — SnapshotContext (inputs, outputs, persistence via sessionStorage)
client/src/hooks/       — useSnapshot, useAuth, useQBO, useCalc
client/src/utils/       — api.js (fetch wrapper), format.js
server/routes/          — Express route handlers (calc, auth, integrations, outputs)
server/calculations/    — Waterfall, ratios, breakeven, forecast, Four Forces
server/integrations/    — QBO, Excel, template writer pipelines
shared/                 — schema.js (INPUT_SHAPE, validation), constants.js
```

## Conventions

- All API calls go through `client/src/utils/api.js`
- SnapshotContext persists inputs and fieldSources to sessionStorage
- Authentication: Supabase Auth with JWTs, authGuard and optionalAuth middleware
- File uploads use express.raw() middleware, not multer
- Server uses ES module imports (import/export, not require)
- Tests use Node.js built-in test runner (node:test) or Jest

## The Four Named Problems (drive all UI copy)

1. The Owner Pay Gap
2. The Breakeven Lie
3. Profit Leaks (Job, Marketing, Overhead)
4. The Scaling Blind Spot
